确诊超560例8州进入紧急状态，美国是否会步意大利后尘？。
With more than 560 confirmed states of emergency, will the United States follow suit?
刘芳。
Liu Fang.
界面新闻                      。
Interface news.
界面新闻。
Interface news.
界面新闻是中国具有影响力的原创财经新媒体，只服务于独立思考的人群。
Interface News is an original and influential new financial media in China, serving only the people who think independently.
2月29日，特朗普在保守派政治行动会议上。
On February 29, Trump spoke at the Conservative Political Action Conference.
来源：特朗普推特记者：刘芳“ “最害怕的还是（在疫情过后）我人没怎么样但是课却没过。
Source: Trump Twitter reporter: "The biggest fear is that (after the outbreak) I'm not all that good but the class isn't.
””不断扩散的新冠肺炎疫情给美国东西海岸人口稠密地区持续带来压力，就连总统特朗普也因参加马里兰州的保守派政治行动会议 (CPAC) 而被推到了聚光灯前。
The spreading outbreak of New Crown Pneumonia continues to put pressure on densely populated parts of the country's east and west coasts, and even President Trump has been pushed into the limelight by his participation in the Conservative Political Action Conference (CPAC) in Maryland.
据疾控中心（CDC）3月8日最新数据显示，美国共确诊新冠肺炎病例565人，死亡22人。
The United States has 565 new cases of pneumonia and 22 deaths, according to new data from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).
有8个州宣布进入紧急状态，其中3个州的感染人数均超过了100人。
Eight states declared a state of emergency, and three of them reported more than 100 infections.
最令人担忧的是，曾在上述会议上和特朗普握手的美国保守派联盟 (ACU) 主席施拉普 (Matt Schlapp) 确认自己曾和新冠肺炎确诊患者有过“非常短暂”的接触。
Most worryingly, Matt Schlapp, chairman of the American Conservative Union (ACU), who shook Trump's hand at the meeting, confirmed that he had had "very brief" contact with patients diagnosed with pneumonia.
不过现年52岁的施拉普并不太担心自己的健康状况。
But Schrapp, 52, isn't too worried about his health.
他在接受电视采访时表示：“我感觉自己健壮得就像马儿一样。
"I feel as strong as a horse," he said in a television interview.
我的孩子们也是。
So are my children.
”2月26日至29日，CPAC在马里兰州的国家港湾举行，特朗普和副总统彭斯等多名共和党政要出席。
From February 26 to 29, the CPAC took place in the National Harbor, Maryland, in the presence of several Republican dignitaries, including Trump and Vice President Burns.
3月7日ACU发表声明称，一名参会人员被确诊感染新冠肺炎，但并没有与特朗普或彭斯接触。
An ACU statement on March 7 said one attendee was diagnosed with pneumonia but had no contact with Trump or Burns.
除了施拉普以外，共和党参议员克鲁兹（Ted Cruz）、戈萨（Paul Gosar）和至少三名国会工作人员也因接触了同一名患者开始进行隔离。
In addition to Schrap, Republican Senators Ted Cruz, Paul Gosar, and at least three members of Congress began isolating themselves after contacting the same patient.
克鲁兹和戈萨均表示，目前没有出现任何症状，隔离只是预防措施。
Both Cruz and Gossa said there were no symptoms and that isolation was a precautionary measure.
特朗普和施拉普握手。
Trump shakes hands with Schlap.
来源：路透社在目前报告疫情的34个州和华盛顿特区中，位于西岸的华盛顿州是疫情的风暴最中心，至少确诊137人。
Source: Reuters is the epicentre of the storm, with at least 137 people diagnosed, in the West Bank state of Washington among the 34 states and Washington, D.C., where the outbreak is currently reported.
在柯克兰市某养老院（Life Care Center of Kirkland），有16名老人因感染新冠肺炎死亡，占全美死亡人数的72%。
At the Life Care Center of Kirkland, 16 elderly people died from pneumonia, accounting for 72% of all deaths nationwide.
据悉，这间养老院一共有老人108名，工作人员180人。
It is reported that the nursing home has a total of 108 elderly people, 180 staff.
《纽约时报》称，目前有至少70名工作人员出现了新冠肺炎的类似症状而正在接受隔离。
The New York Times says at least 70 workers now have similar symptoms of pneumonia and are being quarantined.
2月29日，华盛顿州州长英斯利（Jay Inslee）宣布进入紧急状态。
On February 29, Washington State Governor Jay Inslee declared a state of emergency.
他表示，将动用政府一切必要资源来对抗新冠病毒爆发，如果需要会出动华盛顿州国民警卫队。
He said the government would use all necessary resources to fight the outbreak, if needed, the Washington State National Guard.
Life Care Center of Kirkland一名老人隔着窗户在看自己的丈夫。
Life Care Center of Kirkland An old man was looking at his husband through the window.
来源：people排在全美感染人数第二位的是第一经济大州，加利福尼亚州。
www.youtheme.cn www.youtheme.cn www.youtheme.cn The second most affected state in the United States is California.
《华盛顿邮报》数据显示，加州至少有114人感染，超过1万人正在自我隔离。
At least 114 people in California are infected and more than 10,000 are isolated, according to the Washington Post.
当地时间3月4日，加州州长纽森（Gavin Newsom）宣布进入紧急状态，而载有2383名乘客和1100名船员的“至尊公主号”也于9日停靠在奥克兰港。
California Governor Gavin Newsom declared a state of emergency on March 4, and the Supreme Princess, carrying 2,383 passengers and 1,100 crew members, docked in Auckland on March 9.
届时，如何最大限度地减低社区传播风险将是考验纽森的一道难题。
At that time, how to minimize the risk of community transmission will be a challenge for Newson.
据美联社报道，“至尊公主号”在靠港后将按联邦当局规定花3天时间安排乘客下船。
According to The Associated Press, the Princess Supreme will take three days to disembark after it docks, as required by federal authorities.
最先下船的是有症状和需要医疗护理的人员，其余健康的美国乘客将被送至不同军事基地隔离14天。
The first to disembark were symptomatic and in need of medical care, while the rest of the healthy American passengers would be sent to separate military bases for 14 days.
除此之外，邮轮上来自54个国家的数百名外国乘客将从奥克兰国际机场乘坐包机返回。
In addition, hundreds of foreign passengers from 54 countries aboard the cruise ship will return from Auckland International Airport on charter flights.
中国驻旧金山总领馆透露，“至尊公主”号有11名中国籍工作人员和9名来自大陆的中国公民。
The Chinese Consulate General in San Francisco said the "Supreme Princess" had 11 Chinese crew members and nine Chinese citizens from the mainland.
给纽森带来考验的还不仅是“至尊公主号”。
It was not just the "Supreme Princess" that tested Newson.
受疫情的影响，加州多所知名大学已经停止授课而进入线上模式。
Due to the epidemic, many well-known universities in California have stopped teaching and gone into online mode.
斯坦福大学东亚语言与文化研究博士生黄小谊向界面新闻透露，该大学医学院一名教职员工于3月6日确诊，另有两名学生正在进行隔离并等待筛查结果。
Stanford University doctoral student in East Asian languages and culture Huang Xiaoyi told the Interface News that a faculty member at the university's medical school was confirmed on March 6, and two other students were being quarantined and were awaiting the results of the screening.
黄小谊表示，虽然确诊病例的出现的确让大家感受到紧张，但目前斯坦福大部分人没有佩戴口罩的习惯，自己也更担心学业是否能正常进行的问题：“最害怕的还是（在疫情过后）我人没怎么样但是课却没过。
Wong said that while the emergence of confirmed cases does make people nervous, most people in Stanford do not wear masks and are more worried about whether their studies are going well: "The fear is that I'm not all that good [after the outbreak] but not in class," he said.
”在美国东岸，金融中心纽约的情况不容乐观。
On the east coast, New York, the financial centre, is not doing well.
到发稿为止，纽约州共确诊新冠肺炎患者106人，至少2773人接受隔离。
By the time of writing, 106 new cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in New York state, and at least 2,773 people were quarantined.
3月7日，纽约州州长科莫（Andrew M. Cuomo）宣布全州进入紧急状态。
On March 7, New York Governor Andrew M. Cuomo declared a state of emergency.
对科莫来说，试剂盒短缺是新冠肺炎患者不能及时确诊的最大障碍。
For Komo, the shortage of test kits is the biggest obstacle to timely diagnosis of patients with Newcomore pneumonia.
3月8日，他走访了纽约市长岛的一个实验室(Northwell Health Labs）。
On March 8, he visited a laboratory on Long Island, New York City.
科莫表示，如果获得联邦政府的批准的话，该州的七个实验室便可以立即开始检测新冠肺炎。
Komo said the state's seven laboratories could immediately begin testing for pneumonia if the federal government approves it.
“CDC竟然没有给这个实验室进行授权，这也太离谱和荒谬了”，科莫说，“请醒一醒，让各州私人实验室进行检测，我们需要尽快提高检测能力来辨识出新冠肺炎呈阳性的患者。
"It's outrageous and preposterous that the CDC has not authorized the lab," Komo said. "Wake up and have private laboratories in the states do the tests. We need to improve our detection capabilities as soon as possible to identify patients who are new Crowded Pneumonia.
不使用这个实验室，或其他私人实验室完全没有道理。
There is no reason why this laboratory should not be used, or any other private laboratory.
”纽约州州长科莫在3月8日的新闻发布会上。
New York Governor Timothy Kommer spoke at a news conference on March 8.
来源：《纽约时报》出于对新冠肺炎疫情的担忧，美标准普尔500指数期货在3月9日下跌约5%，盘中一度触发熔断交易。
Sources: Futures for the Standard & Poor's 500-stock index fell about 5% on March 9, triggering a meltdown in the New York Times over the outbreak of pneumonia.
同时下跌的还有道琼斯指数期货，跌幅约为4.9%；纳斯达克综合指数期货下跌4.8%。
Also falling were Dow Jones futures, down about 4.9%, and Nasdaq Composite down 4.8%.
不仅如此，美国10年期国债收益率已跌破0.5%，30年期国债收益率跌破1%。
Moreover, US 10-year Treasury yields have fallen below 0.5%, and 30-year Treasury yields have fallen below 1%.
彭博新闻社表示，这是美国国债收益率曲线有史以来首次跌破这一水平。
Bloomberg said it was the first time the yield curve had fallen below that level.
鉴于疫情的不断升级，美国国立卫生研究院 (NIH)国家过敏和传染病研究所所长福西 (Anthony S. Fauci) 周日表示，美国不排除实施类似意大利一样更为严格的防疫措施。
In the light of the escalating epidemic, Anthony S. Fauci, director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases of the National Institutes of Health, said Sunday that the United States would not rule out more stringent preventive measures like Italy.
“你不想让人们惊慌，但你也看到，疫情的蔓延让一切变得可能，”福西说，“这就是为什么我们必须准备好采取一切适当的行动来控制和缓解疫情的原因。
"You don't want to alarm people, but you also see that the spread of the epidemic makes it possible," Fossi said. "That is why we must be prepared to take all appropriate action to control and mitigate the causes of the outbreak.
